description:
An anthology book about true event in the 70s. 
 
THE BIG BOOK OF THE 70'S is a comprehensive and educational journey back to the most tumultuous and tacky decade of modern history. Using comic strips to revisit the "Me" Era, this entertaining cultural history text looks at the origins and emergence of such oddities as the pet rock, bell bottoms, mood rings, disco, streaking, and running. But at the same time deeper issues like Vietnam, the women's movement, terrorism, and the gasoline shortage are also treated with the respect that they deserve. A roller coaster ride through a time of extreme change and diversity, this book shows not only the fads and phenomena of the seventies but also how they have affected today's society.

Stories include:


He Loves Me! He Loves Me!
The Other Girl
When a Romance Ends
To Walk With Strangers
I Want to Get Married!
name: He Loves Me! He Loves Me!

description: Based on thorough research, THE BIG BOOK OF THE WEIRD WILD WEST presents an unabashed look at the violence, tragedy and strangeness of the American frontier. Using humor and wit to depict tales of cannibalism, gunfights, decapitations, curses, ghosts, cults, lynch mobs, alcoholism, prostitution, and airships, this amusing and informative tome presents the West in an unflattering but accurate fashion. Also included in this black and white comic strip book are the true histories and adventures of such western legends as Jesse James, Doc Holiday, Butch Cassidy, and the infamous Donner Party.

volume.name: The Big Book of the Weird Wild West

description: Distinguishing fact from fiction, THE BIG BOOK OF MARTYRS is a comprehensive study of the most popular and least-known saints who stood firm in their beliefs in the face of persecution. Told through the medium of comic strips, this black and white book documents the lives of religion's greatest heroes in a manner that is both inspirational and educational. Treating this subject matter with the reverence that it deserves, this volume includes the true histories of such legendary martyrs as John the Baptist, St. Agnes, St. Paul, Joan of Arc, St. Thomas More, and Edith Stein.

Whether cursed by fate, stupidity, or genetics, THE BIG BOOK OF LOSERS tells the tales of real people who were forced to endure a damned existence. Exploring the unfortunate adventures of those who could not catch a break, this amazing reference book documents the stories of people who have lost in life, sports, business, and politics. From President Garfield, who died after several incompetent doctors turned a small bullet wound into a huge, festering malady to the woman who burned her husband's life savings in the oven, this tome shows that some people are just destined to come out on the bottom. Also included in this book are the most legendary loser products such as New Coke, the female urinal, and the paper dress.

The girls go to a yard sale and Nibbil finds a big stuffed bunny. That’s great, but Sage finds something even better: a pretty girl to kiss! Will this new girl distract Sage from her pouty mood? Let’s see…young pretty goth girl who wants to get completely naked, in full color, and lick all of Sage’s wonderfully naughty girl spots…yeah, I’d have to say that’s pretty distracting. Of course, Annie and Nibbil are hardly the sorts to simply stand aside when there are girls to kiss! Perky, naughty, cute and downright filthy. And in FULL COLOR!

Hold onto your hat because Dark Horse is galloping forth with a frothy funpack featuring four of today's top cartoonists and a super-rare trading-card insert. Wit-legend Sergio Aragonés kicks off the show with a cover and lead feature introducing an all-new character. Dave Cooper (Hellboy, Jr., Zero Zero) follows with his unique brand of modern jest, and fans of the first ZombieWorld series will applaud the return of Pat McEown to our pages and Jay Stephens (Land of Nod) contributes his playful humor. Guff also features the first ever Meanie Babies story, hot on the heels of the hit trading-card set, by writer Jay Lynch and artist John Pound. This is a "flip book" format, featuring a brand-new painted Meanie Baby cover by John Pound, as well as a rare inserted Meanie Baby card, making this special one-shot the only way for collectors to complete the set.

Eric Quinlan is an average kid whose life is turned upside down when his super-powered parents send him to a summer camp for teenagers with powers. Eric finds himself lost in the woods of Camp Enokchuk, being stalked by three super-villains who believe he really does have super-powers!
name: Where to Begin?
